{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, subspace discrimination enhances the algorithm's adaptability and robustness.",
    "The final step removes the task subspace.",
    "To achieve this, our approach uses SVD reconstruction to reconstitute the modified task matrix, T ′ i from the singular values of T i and singular vectors SV (T ′ i) above.",
    "We can directly subtract the modified task T ′ i, from W ′, or, more generally, subtract a linear smoothing of the task subspaces T ′ i and T i",
    "where α ∈ [0, 1] governs the relative strength of the two UNLEARN matrices (with and without discrimination)."
  ]
}